<body>
<h1>QUIDDITCH FIELD: 3-D  VIEWING
</h1>
<h2>Naga Sai Sri. Kamineni, Prakruthi Burra and Vasudha.V</h2>
<h3>The Scene</h3>
<p>The scene models Quidditch field as described in the Harry Potter books. The scene is enclosed in a cuboid with 5 faces of blue walls and one face, the bottom surface being the field itself.</p>

<h3>Objects in the scene</h3>
<p>The scene contains: </p>
<ul>
<li>A green Quidditch field</li>
<li>Stands (for viewing Quidditch)</li>
<li>Poles with House Flags</li>
<li>Quidditch Poles with loops (to throw the balls through)</li>
<li>Trees</li>
<li>Bats</li>
<li>Trunk</li>
<li>Snitch</li>
<li>Quidditch balls</li>
</ul>
<h3>Primitives used</h3>
<p>
The OpenGL primitives used were:
</p>
<ul>
	<li> Quadrilaterals (GL_QUADS)</li>
	<li> Triangles (GL_TRIANGLES)</li>
	<li> Cylinders (gluCylinder)</li>
	<li> Cones (glutSolidCone)</li>
	<li> Light (GL_LIGHTING)</li>
</ul>
<h3>Translating the Camera</h3>
<dl>
	<dt><b>Panning</b></dt>
	<dd>
		To pan the the camera, use:
		<ul>
			<li> u (up)</li>
			<li> d (down)</li>
			<li> l (left) </li>
			<li> ; (right) </li>
		</ul>
	</dd>
	
	<dt><b>Zooming</b></dt>
	<dd>
		To zoom the camera, use:
		<ul>
			<li> z (zoom in) </li>
			<li> q (zoom out) </li>
		</ul>
	</dd>
</dl>

<h3>Rotating the Camera</h3>
<dl>
	<dt><b>Rolling</b></dt>
  	<dd>
		To roll the camera, use:
		<ul>
			<li> r (counterclockwise about z) </li>
			<li> e (clockwise about z) </li>
		</ul>
	</dd>
	<dt><b>Pitching</b></dt>
	<dd>
		To pitch the camera, use:
		<ul>
			<li> p (counterclockwise about x) </li>
			<li> o (clockwise about x) </li>
		</ul>
	</dd>
	<dt><b>Yawing</b></dt>
	<dd>
		To yaw the camera, use:
		<ul>
			<li> y ( counterclockwise about y) </li>
			<li> t (clockwise about y) </li>
		</ul>
	</dd>
</dl> 

